This directory contains various configuration files for various
elements of ka9q-radio.  They are installed into /etc/radio.

Config files for radiod, the ka9q-radio spectrum server, have names of the form

radiod@instance.conf
or
radiod@instance.conf.d

The first is a plain text file; the second is a directory. The files in the directory
will be concatenated in lexigraphical order and interpreted as though they were part of a
single configuration file.

Run dpkg-reconfigure ka9q-radio to invoke a debconf installer to walk you through the
creation of a minimal radiod config file. It won't define any static receiver channels
but it will be ready for use with applications that create channels dynamically.
